sec.p:
The Regge trajectory is an effective phenomenological approach to describing hadron spectroscopy. A plot between total angular momentum (
J
) and radial quantum number (

    n
    r

) of hadrons against the square of their masses (
M
2
) provides information about the quantum number of a particular state and also helps to identify recently observed states. We use the following definitions:

list-item.p:
                            The (
                            J, M
                            2
                            ) Regge trajectories:
                            
                                (40)
                                
                                    $$\begin{equation}
J = \alpha M^2 + \alpha _{0} .
\end{equation}
$$

